Junior golfer Lee Kimathi won the fourth leg of the U.S. Kids Golf tour tournament at the Karen Country Club. Kimathi carded 75 points in the boys' 15-18 years category, followed closely by Kevin Anyien who took the runners-up position after carding 81 points. In the girls’  8 and under years category, Ashley Gachora and Zianna Khoda both carded an impressive round of 41 points. However, Gachora won the category by virtue of scoring a birdie on the first playoff hole. In the girls’ 13-14 years category, Sanjana Sharma claimed the top position with 83 points followed by Bianca Ngecu, who carded 84 points. James Tino ruled in the boys' under-6 years category after carding an impressive 51 points followed closely by Mohamed Mtsumi with 54 points. In the boys' seven years category, Jeff Kibe claimed top position, carding a round of 48 points. The U.S Kids Golf Tour has so far featured four of the seven events under the tutelage of the Junior Golf Foundation (JGF) Tour with a championship tournament set for May. The remaining three are scheduled to take place at  Karen  ( May 14), Royal Nairobi (May 150 and the Grand Finale at Muthaiga (May 29). 